HEADWORD: encephalartos
<hw>encephalartos</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>any of numerous cycads of the
genus <gen>Encephalartos</gen> having stout cylindrical trunks and a
terminal crown of long, often spiny pinnate leaves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Encephalic</ent>⟦br⟧
